    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I've come across this bug as early as 0.23.5, and can currently reproduce it in 0.28.1\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef gen(**kwargs):\r\n    # Uncomment me to fix crash\r\n    # kwargs = kwargs.copy()\r\n\r\n    gen2(**kwargs)\r\n    yield None\r\n\r\ndef gen2(**kwargs):\r\n    pass\r\n```\r\n\r\nGiven a generator function that accepts `**kwargs`, if it passes those kwargs on to another function call, the program will crash while trying to `INCREF`. Seems a workaround is to copy the kwargs into a different (?) scope.\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> gen()\r\n\r\nProgram received signal SIGSEGV. Segmentation fault.\r\n__pyx_pf_4gen_gen (__pyx_self=<optimized out>, __pyx_v_kwargs=0x0) at gen.c:1181\r\n1181    __Pyx_INCREF(__pyx_cur_scope->__pyx_v_kwargs):\r\n(gdb) bt\r\n#0 __pyx_pf_4gen_gen (__pyx_self=<optimized out>, __pyx_v_kwargs=0x0) at gen.c:1181\r\n#1 __pyx_pw_4gen_1gen (__pyx_self=<optimized out>, __pyx_args=<optimized out>, __pyx_v_kwds=0x0) at gen.c:1159\r\n...\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-19T19:38:42Z",
    "closed_by": {
